2) Second, even if they were the same size, you are giving a `return` after checking the first item. So, if two arrays are not the same, but their first item is the same, you will return true (what is actually happening in your code)

So, what I would say is implementing the following conditions:

 1. Check if length are equal
 2. If length is not equal, return -1
 3. If length is equal, then iterate through the list and compare each number. If the number is not equal, we finish iterating as we know they&#39;re not equal anymore. If the number is equal, keep comparing. You will return true when you reach the end of the list and all elements are equal.

